---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
import Header from "../components/base/Header.astro";
import Footer from "../components/base/Footer.astro";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Rental Requirements"
  description="Driver requirements for renting with 305 Fleet — age, license, insurance, and deposit information."
>
  <Header />

  <main id="main-content" class="flex-1 bg-white">
    <div class="mx-auto max-w-4xl px-4 py-12 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 lg:py-16">
      <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold text-gray-900">Rental Requirements</h1>
      <p class="mt-3 text-lg text-gray-500">
        What you need to rent a vehicle with 305 Fleet.
      </p>

      <div class="mt-8 space-y-8">
        <section class="rounded-xl border border-gray-200 p-6">
          <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-900 flex items-center gap-2">
            <span class="text-2xl">🧑</span> Driver Age
          </h2>
          <p class="mt-3 text-gray-600">
            Renters must be at least <strong>21 years of age</strong>. Some vehicles may require a
            minimum age of 25 — this will be noted on the vehicle listing. Drivers under 25 may be
            subject to additional requirements or surcharges.
          </p>
          <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-gray-500">
            ⓘ Specific age requirements per vehicle will be confirmed at booking.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section class="rounded-xl border border-gray-200 p-6">
          <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-900 flex items-center gap-2">
            <span class="text-2xl">🪪</span> Driver's License
          </h2>
          <p class="mt-3 text-gray-600">
            A valid driver's license is required. We accept:
          </p>
          <ul class="mt-3 ml-6 list-disc text-gray-600 space-y-1">
            <li>Valid US driver's license from any state</li>
            <li>Valid international driver's license (with passport)</li>
            <li>Valid driver's license from your home country (for international visitors)</li>
          </ul>
          <p class="mt-3 text-sm text-gray-500">
            ⓘ License must be valid for the entire rental period. Temporary licenses may be
            accepted with additional verification.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section class="rounded-xl border border-gray-200 p-6">
          <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-900 flex items-center gap-2">
            <span class="text-2xl">🛡️</span> Insurance
          </h2>
          <p class="mt-3 text-gray-600">
            Insurance is required for all rentals. Options include:
          </p>
          <ul class="mt-3 ml-6 list-disc text-gray-600 space-y-1">
            <li><strong>Personal auto insurance</strong> — if your policy covers rental vehicles, we'll verify coverage</li>
            <li><strong>Credit card rental coverage</strong> — some credit cards offer rental car insurance; verify with your card issuer</li>
            <li><strong>Purchased coverage</strong> — insurance options available through our booking platform</li>
          </ul>
          <p class="mt-3 text-sm text-gray-500">
            ⓘ Insurance options and pricing will be presented during the booking process.
            Specific coverage details are determined by the insurance provider, not by 305 Fleet.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section class="rounded-xl border border-gray-200 p-6">
          <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-900 flex items-center gap-2">
            <span class="text-2xl">💳</span> Deposit
          </h2>
          <p class="mt-3 text-gray-600">
            A refundable deposit is required for all rentals. The deposit amount varies by vehicle
            and rental period. The deposit is authorized (not charged) at the time of pickup and
            released after the vehicle is returned in satisfactory condition.
          </p>
          <p class="mt-3 text-sm text-gray-500">
            ⓘ Specific deposit amounts will be confirmed at booking.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section class="rounded-xl border border-gray-200 p-6">
          <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-900 flex items-center gap-2">
            <span class="text-2xl">📋</span> Rental Agreement
          </h2>
          <p class="mt-3 text-gray-600">
            Every rental requires a signed rental agreement. The agreement includes:
          </p>
          <ul class="mt-3 ml-6 list-disc text-gray-600 space-y-1">
            <li>Rental period, rates, and total charges</li>
            <li>Mileage allowance and overage rates</li>
            <li>Insurance coverage selection</li>
            <li>Deposit amount and terms</li>
            <li>Cancellation and modification policy</li>
            <li>Vehicle condition and return requirements</li>
          </ul>
        </section>

        <section class="rounded-xl border border-gray-200 p-6">
          <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-900 flex items-center gap-2">
            <span class="text-2xl">✈️</span> International Visitors
          </h2>
          <p class="mt-3 text-gray-600">
            Welcome to South Florida! International renters are welcome. In addition to the
            standard requirements:
          </p>
          <ul class="mt-3 ml-6 list-disc text-gray-600 space-y-1">
            <li>Passport required for identification</li>
            <li>Driver's license from your home country is accepted</li>
            <li>International Driving Permit (IDP) recommended but not always required</li>
            <li>Insurance options for international travelers are available</li>
          </ul>
          <p class="mt-3 text-sm text-gray-500">
            ⓘ Contact us if you have questions about specific country requirements.
          </p>
        </section>
      </div>

      <div class="mt-8 rounded-lg bg-yellow-50 border border-yellow-300 p-4">
        <p class="text-sm text-yellow-900">
          ⚠️ These requirements are provided for general information. Specific requirements,
          pricing, and policies will be confirmed at the time of booking and are subject to
          change. Wheelbase (our booking platform) is the authority for the current rental terms.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="mt-8 flex justify-center gap-3">
        <a href="/vehicles/" class="inline-flex items-center rounded-lg bg-brand px-6 py-3 text-sm font-semibold text-white hover:bg-brand-light">
          Browse Vehicles
        </a>
        <a href="/rental-policies/" class="inline-flex items-center rounded-lg border border-gray-300 px-6 py-3 text-sm font-semibold text-gray-700 hover:border-brand hover:text-brand">
          View Policies
        </a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </main>

  <Footer />
</BaseLayout>